{"TopicId":196604,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"PartUpgrades needs to acknowledge Localization [Fixed in KSP 1.11]","CreatedByName":"JadeOfMaar","CreatedById":167617,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-29T18:19:09Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"JadeOfMaar","CreatedById":167617,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-29T18:19:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI know a few great mods, and their makers, who make ample use of the \u003Cstrong\u003Eunder-developed\u003C/strong\u003E part upgrade system.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGiven the case, it\u0027s worth pointing out that the upgrade system (a forgotten feature in \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/66485-squad/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002266485\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/66485-squad/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@SQUAD\u003C/a\u003E \u0027s eyes) doesn\u0027t acknowledge localization which is quite a bother. I\u0027m not asking for any focus to be turned towards building it up...I\u0027m only asking for this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022IOI5nUM.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002264.33\u0022 height=\u0022330\u0022 width=\u0022513\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/IOI5nUM.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSome large mods that use this system:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nB9 Part Switch (expands on this system\u0027s abilities)\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nBluedog Design Bureau\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nOPT Spaceplane\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nWild Blue Industries (suite)\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-01-03T16:36:43Z\u0022 title=\u002201/03/2021 04:36  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 3, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by JadeOfMaar\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"hemeac","CreatedById":59783,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-09T05:35:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI thought it was something with my install that broke the default part upgrades.\u00A0 Have you submitted a bug ticket for that?\u00A0 I hadn\u0027t seen anything related, but can submit one if you haven\u0027t.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JadeOfMaar","CreatedById":167617,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-09T20:44:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/59783-hemeac/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002259783\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/59783-hemeac/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@hemeac\u003C/a\u003E No I haven\u0027t made a support ticket. Be my guest. The issue is simply: The upgrade system existed long before localization did, and wasn\u0027t updated to understand it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-09T21:32:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI wonder if a post module manager process could actually go through the entire module manager. config cache and do all the localization changes at that time\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"hemeac","CreatedById":59783,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-09T23:55:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223851618\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022196604\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221599687141\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022linuxgurugamer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, linuxgurugamer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI wonder if a post module manager process could actually go through the entire module manager. config cache and do all the localization changes at that time\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWill need to test that idea after work.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn the mean time, raised the issue:\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://bugs.kerbalspaceprogram.com/issues/26055\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://bugs.kerbalspaceprogram.com/issues/26055\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"hemeac","CreatedById":59783,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-01-03T11:14:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/167617-jadeofmaar/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022167617\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/167617-jadeofmaar/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@JadeOfMaar\u003C/a\u003E, just in case you missed this, this was fixed in 1.11\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/kerbal-forum-uploads/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JadeOfMaar","CreatedById":167617,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-01-03T13:03:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExcellent! \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}